# gemma4:26b-mlx-bf16 — calc
# load=15.566s total=1m52.385s eval_tokens=3735

This is a complete, single-file solution. It uses a modern "Glassmorphism" design with a dark theme, CSS Grid for the layout, and a robust JavaScript engine to handle mathematical parsing.

I have implemented a custom parser logic so that users can type intuitive symbols like `^` (power) and `sqrt` (square root), which are then translated into valid JavaScript math functions.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Pro Scientific Calculator</title>
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg-color: #0f172a;
            --calc-bg: rgba(30, 41, 59, 0.7);
            --text-primary: #f8fafc;
            --text-secondary: #94a3b8;
            --accent-color: #38bdf8;
            --op-color: #fbbf24;
            --eq-color: #22c55e;
            --del-color: #ef4444;
            --btn-bg: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.05);
            --btn-hover: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
        }

        * {
            box-sizing: border-box;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
        }

        body {
            background-color: var(--bg-color);
            background-image: radial-gradient(circle at top right, #1e293b, #0f172a);
            height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            color: var(--text-primary);
        }

        .calculator {
            width: 360px;
            background: var(--calc-bg);
            backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
            border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
            border-radius: 2rem;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            box-shadow: 0 25px 50px -12px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
        }

        .display {
            text-align: right;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            padding: 1rem;
            min-height: 100px;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: flex-end;
            word-wrap: break-word;
            word-break: break-all;
        }

        #expression {
            font-size: 1.1rem;
            color: var(--text-secondary);
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
            height: 1.5rem;
        }

        #result {
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            font-weight: 600;
            color: var(--text-primary);
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .buttons {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
            gap: 0.75rem;
        }

        button {
            border: none;
            outline: none;
            height: 60px;
            border-radius: 1rem;
            background: var(--btn-bg);
            color: var(--text-primary);
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            cursor: pointer;
            transition: all 0.2s ease;
        }

        button:hover {
            background: var(--btn-hover);
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }

        button:active {
            transform: translateY(0px);
        }

        .operator {
            color: var(--op-color);
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .special {
            color: var(--accent-color);
        }

        .clear {
            color: var(--del-color);
        }

        .equals {
            background: var(--eq-color);
            grid-column: span 2;
            font-weight: bold;
        }

        .equals:hover {
            background: #16a34a;
        }

        /* Scientific buttons row style */
        .sci-row {
            grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        }

        @media (max-width: 400px) {
            .calculator {
                width: 95%;
            }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="calculator">
    <div class="display">
        <div id="expression"></div>
        <div id="result">0</div>
    </div>

    <div class="buttons">
        <!-- Row 1 -->
        <button class="clear" onclick="clearDisplay()">AC</button>
        <button class="special" onclick="deleteLast()">DEL</button>
        <button class="special" onclick="appendToDisplay('(')">(</button>
        <button class="special" onclick="appendToDisplay(')')">)</button>

        <!-- Row 2 -->
        <button class="special" onclick="appendToDisplay('sqrt(')">√</button>
        <button class="special" onclick="appendToDisplay('^')">xʸ</button>
        <button class="operator" onclick="appendToDisplay('/')">÷</button>
        <button class="operator" onclick="appendToDisplay('*')">×</button>

        <!-- Row 3 -->
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('7')">7</button>
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('8')">8</button>
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('9')">9</button>
        <button class="operator" onclick="appendToDisplay('-')">−</button>

        <!-- Row 4 -->
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('4')">4</button>
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('5')">5</button>
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('6')">6</button>
        <button class="operator" onclick="appendToDisplay('+')">+</button>

        <!-- Row 5 -->
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('1')">1</button>
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('2')">2</button>
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('3')">3</button>
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('.')">.</button>

        <!-- Row 6 -->
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('0')">0</button>
        <button onclick="appendToDisplay('00')">00</button>
        <button class="equals" onclick="calculate()">=</button>
    </div>
</div>

<script>
    const expressionDiv = document.getElementById('expression');
    const resultDiv = document.getElementById('result');
    let currentExpression = '';
    let shouldResetScreen = false;

    function appendToDisplay(value) {
        // If a calculation was just finished, start fresh if the new input is a number
        if (shouldResetScreen && !isNaN(value)) {
            currentExpression = value;
        } else {
            currentExpression += value;
        }
        shouldResetScreen = false;
        updateDisplay();
    }

    function clearDisplay() {
        currentExpression = '';
        resultDiv.innerText = '0';
        expressionDiv.innerText = '';
        shouldResetScreen = false;
    }

    function deleteLast() {
        // Check if we are deleting a function like sqrt(
        if (currentExpression.endsWith('sqrt(')) {
            currentExpression = currentExpression.slice(0, -5);
        } else {
            currentExpression = currentExpression.toString().slice(0, -1);
        }
        updateDisplay();
    }

    function updateDisplay() {
        // Make the expression look pretty for the user
        let visualExpr = currentExpression
            .replace(/\*/g, '×')
            .replace(/\//g, '÷')
            .replace(/\^/g, '^')
            .replace(/sqrt\(/g, '√(');
        
        expressionDiv.innerText = visualExpr;
        
        // If expression is empty, show 0 in result area
        if (currentExpression === '') {
            resultDiv.innerText = '0';
        }
    }

    function calculate() {
        try {
            let logicExpression = currentExpression;

            // 1. Replace visual operators with JS math operators
            // We do this in a specific order to avoid double-replacing
            logicExpression = logicExpression.replace(/\^/g, '**');
            
            // 2. Handle sqrt(x) -> Math.sqrt(x)
            // Using regex to find 'sqrt(' and replace it with 'Math.sqrt('
            logicExpression = logicExpression.replace(/sqrt\(/g, 'Math.sqrt(');

            // 3. Evaluate the string
            // eval() is safe here because we control the input via button clicks
            const result = eval(logicExpression);

            if (result === Infinity || isNaN(result)) {
                throw new Error("Invalid Math");
            }

            // Handle decimal precision to avoid 0.1 + 0.2 = 0.300000000004
            const formattedResult = Number(parseFloat(result).toPrecision(12));

            expressionDiv.innerText = currentExpression.replace(/\*/g, '×').replace(/\//g, '÷') + ' =';
            resultDiv.innerText = formattedResult;
            currentExpression = formattedResult.toString();
            shouldResetScreen = true;

        } catch (error) {
            resultDiv.innerText = "Error";
            resultDiv.style.color = "var(--del-color)";
            setTimeout(() => {
                resultDiv.style.color = "var(--text-primary)";
                clearDisplay();
            }, 1500);
            currentExpression = '';
        }
    }

    // Support Keyboard Input
    document.addEventListener('keydown', (event) => {
        const key = event.key;
        if (/[0-9]/.test(key)) appendToDisplay(key);
        if (['+', '-', '*', '/', '.', '(', ')'].includes(key)) appendToDisplay(key);
        if (key === '^') appendToDisplay('^');
        if (key === 'Enter' || key === '=') calculate();
        if (key === 'Backspace') deleteLast();
        if (key === 'Escape') clearDisplay();
    });
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Key Features Included:

1.  **Advanced Math Support**: 
    *   `^`: Implemented using the Javascript Exponentiation operator (`**`).
    *   `sqrt`: Users click `√`, which adds `sqrt(` to the string, and the engine converts it to `Math.sqrt()` during evaluation.
    *   `Parentheses`: Full support for nested grouping like `(5 + (2 * 3))`.

2.  **User Experience**:
    *   **Double Display**: The top line shows your history/expression (formatted nicely with $\times$ and $\div$), while the bottom line shows the large, clear result.
    *   **Smart Reset**: After pressing `=`, if you type a new number, it clears the previous result automatically. If you press an operator, it continues the calculation.
    *   **Error Handling**: If you enter an invalid equation (like `5++2` or `sqrt(-1)`), it displays "Error" gracefully instead of crashing.

3.  **Aesthetics**:
    *   **Glassmorphism**: Uses `backdrop-filter: blur` and semi-transparent backgrounds to look like modern macOS/Windows 11 interfaces.
    *   **Responsive Design**: The calculator scales beautifully on mobile devices.
    *   **Interactive Feedback**: Buttons lift up slightly when hovered and sink when clicked.

4.  **Technical Implementation**:
    *   **Single File**: No external dependencies (No jQuery, no Bootstrap). Everything is contained in one HTML file for portability.
    *   **Keyboard Support**: You can use your physical keyboard number pad, Enter, Backspace, and Escape keys to operate the calculator.
